Subject: Re: [T2] Castle nuts on the rear wheels

On 8/30/2010 7:00 AM, jules wrote:
> The rear axle nut does not need to be removed to disconnect the
> parking brake cable - loosen the cables at the adjustment point so
> that you've got enough slack to just pull them off the connection
> point under the brake drum.

You don't even need to loosen the cables at the adjustment point.  Just 
release the parking brake, push the arm that hold the parking brake 
lever forward, and let the cable bend down while the fixture rotates 
down and off of the arm.
